 We know that two primes are roots of a quadratic, then it is a一轮完全平方。 In this equation $x^2-12x+k$, there is a middle term $-12$, and it is half of the product of the two roots, squared. Hence, the product of roots is $12^2=144$ and (by Vieta's formulas) their sum is $12$. We have $\left( \text{root1} + \text{root2} \right)\left( \text{root1} \times \text{root2} \right) = \text{product of roots}$. Then we use the fact that two primes are sum =product + 1. Hence, \begin{align*} 
k &= 144 \times 12 + 144 - 12^2 \\ \Rightarrow \qquad k &= 576 + 144 - 144 \\ \Rightarrow \qquad k &= \boxed{576}. 
\end{align*}
